Think of time evolution as a rotation in the dual lane manifold:
•	Linearity says the rotation acts uniformly on all components of a superposition.
•	Unitarity says the rotation preserves lengths, angles, and the symplectic 2 form.

Together:
Time is a symmetry of the informational geometry.
This is why the Higgs vector stays fixed, why mass is stable, and why the SM gauge group emerges cleanly at the boundary.




